text: New Hythe is a village in mid-Kent, England. It is on the banks of the River Medway. It is about 5 miles from Maidstone. Its name is from the Old English word Hythe, meaning haven or landing place, It also has a mill. It has a railway station called New Hythe railway station. ==Other websites== Category:Kent boroughs Category:Villages in Kent
